# Regression: observer state (Env::obs — per-slot entropy/dH) is part of binding
# identity, so a parked-and-reused call env must reset it (vm_park_call_env).
# Otherwise a windowed predicate on an observed LOCAL reads the PREVIOUS call's
# trajectory: a function with fewer than the window's worth of observed assigns
# silently "converges" on its 2nd invocation by inheriting the 1st call's
# samples. The window is 10.

# #412 note: the settling value is 0.001, NOT 1.0 — unity is the entropy
# HORIZON now (H = 1.0 there, >= h_low), so nothing parked at exactly 1.0 can
# classify converged; 0.001 sits in the low-entropy home region (H ~ 0.011).

# (a) DRIFT GUARD: 6 observed assigns/call (< 10) must NEVER fill the window,
#     no matter how many times the function is called on a recycled env.
define few() as:
    local x is 0.001
    x is 0.001
    x is 0.001
    x is 0.001
    x is 0.001
    x is 0.001
    return converged of x
local a1 is few of null
local a2 is few of null
local a3 is few of null

# (b) WITHIN-CALL GUARD: a full window in a SINGLE call must still converge —
#     every time, including on the reused env — so the park-reset doesn't
#     over-correct and suppress legitimate convergence.
define many() as:
    local y is 0.001
    y is 0.001
    y is 0.001
    y is 0.001
    y is 0.001
    y is 0.001
    y is 0.001
    y is 0.001
    y is 0.001
    y is 0.001
    y is 0.001
    y is 0.001
    return converged of y
local b1 is many of null
local b2 is many of null

if (a1 == 0) and (a2 == 0) and (a3 == 0) and (b1 == 1) and (b2 == 1):
    print of "OBS_PARK_OK"
else:
    print of "OBS_PARK_FAIL a="
    print of a1
    print of a2
    print of a3
    print of "b="
    print of b1
    print of b2
